data.chText: 板岩；石板
data.enText: a type of dark grey stone that splits easily into thin flat layers

data.chText: 板岩采石场
data.enText: a slate quarry

data.chText: 大海的颜色像石板。
data.enText: The sea was the colour of slate.

data.chText: （盖房顶的）石板瓦
data.enText: a small thin piece of slate , used for covering roofs

data.chText: 一块松动的石板瓦从房顶上掉了下来。
data.enText: A loose slate had fallen from the roof.

data.enText: the Democratic slate

data.enText: a small sheet of slate in a wooden frame, used in the past in schools for children to write on
a clean sheet/slate

data.chText: 无过错记录；清白的历史
data.enText: a record of your work or behaviour that does not show any mistakes or bad things that you have done

data.chText: 没有任何政府执政一点也不失误。
data.enText: No government operates with a completely clean sheet.

data.chText: 他们在比赛中保持了未失一分的纪录。
data.enText: They kept a clean sheet in the match (= no goals were scored against them) .
wipe the slate clean

data.chText: 把以往过错一笔勾销；一消前愆；捐弃前嫌
data.enText: to agree to forget about past mistakes or arguments and start again with a relationship

data.chText: （尤指在报纸上）批评，抨击
data.enText: to criticize sb/sth, especially in a newspaper

data.chText: 批评一部书 / 一出戏 / 一位作家
data.enText: to slate a book/play/writer

data.chText: 预定；计划；安排
data.enText: to plan that sth will happen at a particular time in the future

data.chText: 这些房子在五年前就确定要拆除了。
data.enText: The houses were first slated for demolition five years ago.

data.chText: 新商店预计春天开业。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.enText: The new store is slated to open in spring.

data.chText: 推举；选定
data.enText: to suggest or choose sb for a job, position, etc.

data.chText: 我听说，我被定为提升的人选。
data.enText: I was told that I was being slated for promotion.

data.chText: 他获选在新的音乐剧中担任主角。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.enText: He is slated to play the lead in the new musical.

tr: (formerly) a writing tablet made of slate
a list of candidates nominated by a political party to run for election to public offices
a fine-grained metamorphic rock that can be split into thin layers
thin layers of rock used for roofing

example: He slated his talk for 9 AM
She was slated to be his successor

tr: enter on a list or slate for an election
example: He was slated for borough president

value.def: Slate is a dark grey rock that can be easily split into thin layers. Slate is often used for covering roofs.

example.ex: ... a stone-built cottage, with a traditional slate roof.
example.tran: 传统石板瓦屋顶的石屋

value.def: A slate is one of the small flat pieces of slate that are used for covering roofs.
A slate is a list of candidates for an election, usually from the same party.

example.ex: The leadership want to present a single slate of candidates to be approved in an open vote.
example.tran: 领导层打算只提交一份供公开投票表决通过的候选人名单。

value.def: If something is slated to happen, it is planned to happen at a particular time or on a particular occasion.

example.ex: Bromfield was slated to become U.S. Secretary of Agriculture...
example.tran: 布罗姆菲尔德被确定为美国农业部长。

example.ex: Controversial energy measures are slated for Senate debate within days.
example.tran: 几项颇受争议的能源措施定于几天后提交参议院讨论。

value.def: If something is slated, it is criticized very severely.

example.ex: Arnold Schwarzenegger's new restaurant has been slated by a top food critic...
example.tran: 阿诺德·施瓦辛格的新餐馆受到了一位顶级食评家的恶评。

example.ex: Slated by critics at the time, the film has since become a cult classic.
example.tran: 尽管在当时备受评论家的非议，这部影片后来却成了一部有关异端邪教的经典之作。

value.def: If you start with a clean slate, you do not take account of previous mistakes or failures and make a fresh start.

example.ex: The proposal is to pay everything you owe, so that you can start with a clean slate.
example.tran: 建议你还清所有的债务，这样你就能够重新开始了。

value.def: If you wipe the slate clean, you decide to forget previous mistakes, failures, or debts and to start again.

example.ex: Why not wipe the slate clean and start all over again?
example.tran: 为什么不洗心革面、从头来过呢？
